text: [Music]
what's the matter now glad you asked I
just come home from a long day of work I
had a coplo of meetings I had a million
emails from my boss I had a ton of
spreadsheets I had to update do you know
what I didn't have today what a single
damn text from you I knew you'd be busy
let me get this straight at no point
today didn't you feel the need to check
up on me or just tell me you love me
well let me explain what happens inside
my head when I don't hear from you all
damn day long stage one I begin to worry
that something happened to you stage two
I begin to think of you home with
another woman stage three I prepare to
find you home with said woman stage four
I talk myself off that ledge by eating
my weight in peanut M&M's stage five I
feel extreme guilt for eating so much so
I go through an entire self-loading
battle where I finally decide to aim my
frustration towards you stage six I
finally decide I'm going to be a bigger
person and say nothing and just slam all
the doors in the house so that you
finally ask me what's wrong Mom this is
not healthy you can't be bothered to
send a simple text saying I love you
babe I don't have to text you all the
time to let you know that I love I'm
going to let you sleep on that
